# Force LF line endings for all text files on checkout, on every OS.
# The windows-latest CI runner defaults to core.autocrlf=true; without this,
# it would check out CRLF and `prettier --check` (LF, Prettier's default
# endOfLine) would fail on every file — an OS-dependent false red.
# Binary exceptions (e.g. FITS/XISF fixtures) get added here as they arrive.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Fixture binaries (P0-06): git must never rewrite bytes (e.g. CRLF conversion
# on Windows checkouts) or every determinism/structure test fails on one CI leg.
*.fits binary
*.xisf binary
*.cr2 binary
*.cr3 binary
*.nef binary
*.arw binary
